    "long_instructions": "# Titanic Survival\r\n\r\n::: details [**✅ Step 1**]\r\n**Explore the Dataset**\r\n- Run the starter code to explore the dataset using `info()`, `describe()` and `head()`.\r\n- Begin thinking about which of the attributes you might want to use to uncover insights into the question: ***How did survival on the Titanic vary by class, and how did the average fares differ across these classes?***\r\n:::\r\n\r\n::: details [**✅ Step 2**]\r\n**Group the data:**\r\n- Think about how survival and class might have influenced the fares. How could you use a stacked bar chart to visualize this relationship?\r\n:::\r\n\r\n::: details [**✅ Step 3**]\r\n**Generate the Stacked Bar Chart:**\r\n- Use `stacked_data.plot` to create the chart\r\n- Use `plt.legend`, `plt.xticks`, `plt.xlabel`, `plt.ylabel`, and `plt.title` to label the chart\r\n- *You might also find it helpful to add a legend to clarify survival information*\r\n- Use `plt.show` to display the chart\r\n:::\r\n\r\n::: details [**✅ Step 4**]\r\n**Interpret the Stacked Bar Chart:**\r\n- What does the chart reveal about the variation in survival on the Titanic by class? \r\n- How do the average fares differ across these classes and survival statuses?\r\n:::\r\n\r\n\r\n",
