    "teacher_markdown": "**What Students Should Take Away:**\r\n- Understanding Grouping and Visualization: Students should understand how to use groupby() and unstack() to organize data for a stacked bar chart, visualizing the relationship between passenger class, survival, and average fare.\r\n- Interpreting Stacked Bar Charts: Students should be able to interpret the stacked bar chart to uncover insights about survival rates and fare differences across classes.\r\n\r\n\r\n**Misconceptions Students Might Have or Points They Might Struggle With and Tips to Assist:**\r\n- Students might think that unstack() is an unnecessary step, without realizing its role in organizing data for a stacked bar chart.\r\n  - Tip: Encourage students to compare the output with and without unstack() and discuss how it reshapes the data for effective visualization.\r\n- Students may have difficulty understanding how survival and class influenced fares and how to represent this in a stacked bar chart.\r\n  - Tip: Guide students to think about historical and social factors that might have influenced survival rates and fares. Use discussion questions to help them connect these factors to the data.\r\n\r\n",
    "display_name": "Titanic Survival",
    "bubble_choice_description": "Practice creating a **stacked bar chart** to answer a question about the Titanic!",
